0Fraud%20was%20rampant%2C%20and%20the%20government%20lost%20an%20estimated%20%24300%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20Republicans%20Sen.%20Joni%20Ernst%20and%20Rep.%20Roger%20Williams%20introduced%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20give%20prosecutors%20additional%20time%20to%20bring%20charges%20of%20defrauding%20two%20of%20these%20lesser-known%20pandemic%20bailouts%3A%20the%20%2428.6%20billion%20Restaurant%20Revitalization%20Fund%20and%20the%20%2414.6%20billion%20Shuttered%20Venue%20Operators%20Grant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErnst's%20office%20cited%20a%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flil-wayne-chris-brown-covid-relief-funds-svog-grant-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%20investigation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20found%20that%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20flowed%20from%20the%20Shuttered%20Venues%20program%20to%20some%20of%20America's%20most%20successful%20musicians%2C%20including%20Lil%20Wayne%2C%20Alice%20in%20Chains%2C%20Marshmello%20and%20Chris%20Brown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20bill%20passes%2C%20the%20timeline%20to%20bring%20charges%20would%20extend%20to%2010%20years.%20Ordinarily%2C%20prosecutors%20have%20five%20years%20to%20bring%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFraudsters%20were%20let%20off%20the%20hook%20for%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20new%20sheriff%20in%20town%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ernst%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThese%20bad%20actors%20stole%20billions%20in%20relief%20that%20were%20meant%20for%20hardworking%20small%20businesses%20struggling%20to%20keep%20their%20doors%20open.%20I%20am%20ensuring%20that%20every%20last%20criminal%20is%20held%20accountable%20and%20taxpayers%20get%20their%20money%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20comes%20three%20weeks%20after%20a%20federal%20watchdog%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fassets%2Fgao-25-107753.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20the%20restaurant%20fund%20%E2%80%94%20%249%20billion%20%E2%80%94%20was%20paid%20out%20improperly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawmakers%20made%20attempts%20to%20safeguard%20pandemic%20aid%20funds.%20They%20set%20aside%20%2425%20million%20from%20a%20%242.2%20trillion%20pandemic-relief%20law%20in%20March%202020%20to%20set%20up%20the%20Special%20Inspector%20General%20for%20Pandemic%20Recovery%2C%20and%20set%20aside%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20more%20for%20the%20IRS.%20They%20also%20gave%20prosecutors%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpandemicoversight.gov%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fpresident-biden-signs-legislation-giving-watchdogs-more-time-fight-pandemic-fraud%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPresident%2520Biden%2520signed%2520H.R.%2Cin%2520most%2520of%2520these%2520cases.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextra%20five%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20bring%20charges%20when%20people%20defrauded%20two%20of%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration's%20key%20assistance%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20said%20in%20a%20report%20last%20April%20that%20over%203%2C000%20people%20had%20been%20charged%20relating%20to%20the%20abuse%20of%20over%20%241%20billion%20in%20pandemic%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelly%20Loeffler%2C%20who%20was%20named%20by%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20to%20lead%20the%20SBA%2C%20has%20said%20that%20pursuing%20fraud%20is%20one%20of%20her%20top%20priorities.%20She%20has%20said%20the%20Biden%20administration%20improperly%20reduced%20safeguards%20around%20the%20agency's%20lending%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20the%20SBA%20has%20said%20it%20will%20cut%20its%20staff%20by%2043%25%2C%20taking%20it%20back%20to%20pre-pandemic%20staffing%20levels.%20The%20agency's%20inspector%20general%2C%20its%20internal%20watchdog%2C%20was%20among%20several%20anti-fraud%20officials%20fired%20by%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20SBA%20representative%20didn't%20reply%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20inspector%20general's%20office%2C%20known%20as%20SIGPR%2C%20quietly%20closed%20its%20doors%20after%20Congress%20failed%20to%20pass%20legislation%20that%20would%20extend%20its%20mandate.%20The%20office%20had%20fewer%20than%2060%20staffers%20and%20its%20numbers%20shrank%20as%20its%20closing%20date%20approached%2C%20according%20to%20one%20of%20its%20final%20monthly%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENennette%20Day%2C%20a%20retired%20special%20agent%20who%20served%20at%20SIGPR%2C%20said%20that%20even%20if%20deadlines%20to%20bring%20charges%20are%20extended%2C%20competing%20enforcement%20priorities%20and%20a%20loss%20of%20investigative%20momentum%20could%20frustrate%20efforts%20to%20hold%20pandemic%20wrongdoers%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20those%20cases%20had%20to%20get%20switched%20to%20another%20agency%2C%20which%20I'll%20tell%20you%20right%20now%2C%20from%20experience%2C%20almost%20always%20kills%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20March%2C%20Congressman%20Jason%20Smith%2C%20a%20Missouri%20Republican%20who%20leads%20the%20House%20committee%20that%20prepares%20spending%20bills%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwaysandmeans.house.gov%2F2025%2F03%2F26%2Fone-day-left-shot-clock-about-to-expire-on-prosecuting-those-who-stole-billions-in-pandemic-unemployment-benefits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eurged%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Senate%20to%20take%20action%20on%20a%20measure%20that%20would%20give%20prosecutors%20more%20time%20to%20go%20after%20unemployment-aid%20fraud.%20About%20%24135%20billion%20was%20lost%20to%20criminals%2C%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Know%20more%3F%20Reach%20Jack%20Newsham%20via%20email%20(%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajnewsham%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ejnewsham%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E)%20or%20via%20Signal