ther%20options%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-retirement-job-loss-fired-six-figure-salary-layoffs-work-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edwindling%20severance%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20need%20for%20health%20insurance%20for%20my%20family%20meant%20I%20had%20to%20take%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20in%20the%20Hudson%20Valley%2C%20which%20meant%20I'd%20be%20commuting%202%20%C2%BD%20hours%20one%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e10deebb-0f5f-40b0-8b7e-f9e4cc0cab77%5C%22%3EMy%20new%20commute%20threw%20everything%20off%20balance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20leave%20home%20in%20the%20mornings%20before%20the%20sun%20rose%20and%20my%20daughter%20was%20awake%20and%20not%20see%20her%20until%2012%20hours%20later%2C%20when%20she%20was%20about%20to%20go%20to%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20needed%20to%20cut%20some%20days%20short%20at%20his%20job%20so%20he%20could%20make%20it%20to%20daycare%20on%20time.%20Sometimes%20he%20couldn't%2C%20and%20we%20needed%20to%20scramble%20to%20find%20someone%20to%20scoop%20our%20girl%20up%20at%20the%20last%20minute%20since%20I'd%20be%20stuck%20on%20a%20subway%20or%20train.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20a%20year%20driving%20across%20the%20Hudson%20River%20to%20the%20Metro-North%20station%2C%20riding%20the%20train%20for%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20into%20Grand%20Central%2C%20taking%20the%20subway%20down%20to%20the%20financial%20district%2C%20and%20walking%20a%20half%20mile%20to%20my%20office%20two%20to%20three%20days%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20to%20sit%20at%20my%20desk%2C%20write%20and%20edit%2C%20not%20talk%20to%20many%20people%2C%20and%20do%20it%20all%20over%20again%20for%20the%20journey%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22959a8c7c-eb59-4b75-9341-6c469273e4f1%5C%22%3EIf%20you%20think%20this%20seems%20ridiculous%2C%20it's%20because%20it%20is%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20need%20to%20be%20in%20a%20physical%20office%20to%20write%20and%20edit%20%E2%80%94%20and%20very%20often%2C%20I%20walked%20into%20an%20office%20that%20was%20at%20best%2C%20half%20full%2C%20and%20at%20worst%2C%20mostly%20rows%20of%20empty%20desks%2C%20making%20me%20feel%20like%20the%20four%20to%20five%20hours%20a%20day%20I%20was%20spending%20on%20trains%20and%20not%20with%20my%20family%20was%20a%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20was%20the%20point%20of%20a%20hybrid%20work%20schedule%20if%20people%20didn't%20always%20show%20up%3F%20Why%20was%20I%20spending%20so%20much%20time%20traveling%20so%20I%20could%20work%20at%20my%20desk%20and%20barely%20speak%20to%20anyone%20there%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20I%20was%20sitting%20next%20to%20someone%20in%20the%20office%20or%20working%20from%20home%2C%20all%20communication%20was%20done%20over%20Slack.%20Zoom%20calls%20still%20happened%20as%20well%2C%20even%20while%20in%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22db488f4c-8a8f-4b15-a994-30d5978c9fef%5C%22%3EI%20knew%20I%20had%20to%20make%20a%20big%20change%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20have%20that%20precious%20time%20back%20with%20my%20daughter%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20talking%20about%20just%20applying%20for%20a%20new%20job%20type%20of%20change.%20I%20mean%20a%20larger%20pivot%20away%20from%20journalism%2C%20since%20I%20couldn't%20find%20anything%20that%20was%20fully%20remote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20pivot%20was%20difficult%20for%20me%20because%20I'm%20very%20proud%20of%20my%20journalism%20career%2C%20but%20spending%20time%20with%20my%20daughter%20was%20more%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20applied%20for%20content%20marketing%20roles%20at%20remote-friendly%20companies.%20I'll%20be%20honest%2C%20most%20of%20the%20roles%20I%20applied%20for%20did%20not%20follow%20up%2C%20which%20was%20disheartening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20fintech%20company%20took%20a%20chance%20on%20me%20%E2%80%94%20one%20with%20a%20fully%20remote%2C%20parent-friendly%20culture%20that%20means%20that%20I%20can%20drop%20my%20daughter%20off%20and%20pick%20her%20up%20at%20school.%3C%2Fp