%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20for%20India%20and%20China%2C%20two%20ancient%20civilisations%20seeking%20economic%20and%20strategic%20adjustments%20in%20modern%20times%2C%20was%20how%20to%20craft%20a%20relationship%20that%20while%20minimising%20the%20possibility%20of%20conflict%2C%20could%20take%20advantage%20of%20opportunities%20for%20cooperation%20and%20manage%20the%20competition%20that%20is%20natural%20for%20growing%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20India-China%20border%20has%20been%20relatively%20peaceful%20since%20the%20end%20of%20the%20war%20in%201962.%20Both%20countries%20attached%20priority%20to%20economic%20growth.%20To%20avoid%20miscalculation%20on%20the%20border%2C%20India%20and%20China%20signed%20bilateral%20agreements%20on%20maintenance%20of%20peace%20and%20tranquility%2C%20confidence-building%20measures%20and%20guiding%20principles%20to%20address%20the%20outstanding%20boundary%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20noteworthy%20that%20even%20during%20the%20recent%20skirmishes%2C%20which%20saw%20%E2%80%9Cgrey%20zone%E2%80%9D%20conflict%2C%20neither%20side%20allowed%20the%20situation%20to%20escalate%20to%20a%20full-blown%20war.%20Both%20remained%20committed%20to%20dialogue%20and%20understood%20that%20the%20opposing%20side%20could%20not%20be%20contained.%20Political%20will%20and%20trust%20would%20be%20necessary%20to%20maintain%20peace%20across%20the%20Himalayas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20Asian%20Century%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20modern%20nations%2C%20both%20have%20risen%20as%20powers%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20geoeconomic%20and%20geopolitical%20shifts.%20Today%2C%20China%20is%20the%20second%20largest%20economy%2C%20while%20India%20will%20soon%20be%20the%20third%20largest%2C%20besides%20being%20the%20two%20most%20populous%20countries.%20The%20future%20provides%20an%20opportunity%20to%20shape%20an%20emerging%20Asian%20century%20and%20for%20transformation%20in%20global%20governance%20that%20is%20representative%20and%20inclusive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%201990%2C%20bilateral%20trade%20has%20grown%20from%20a%20mere%20%2450%20million%20to%20over%20%24100%20billion.%20Imports%20of%20cheap%20Chinese%20goods%20have%20fed%20value%20chains%20and%20infrastructure%20projects%20in%20India%20but%20have%20also%20weakened%20domestic%20industry%2C%20while%20India's%20exports%2C%20primarily%20raw%20materials%2C%20have%20been%20sluggish%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20trade%20imbalance.%20Bilateral%20investments%20have%20not%20grown%20in%20a%20similar%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20India-China%20Joint%20Study%20Group%20report%20highlighted%20the%20benefits%20of%20cooperation%20but%20also%20pointed%20out%20the%20complementary%20nature%20of%20the%20two%20economies.%20This%20has%20inhibited%20participation%20in%20bilateral%20or%20regional%20free%20trade%20agreements.%20Post-Galwan%20export%20restrictions%20and%20investment%20wariness%20by%20China%2C%20the%20scrutiny%20of%20Chinese%20investments%20by%20India%20and%20travel%20restrictions%20imposed%20by%20both%20sides%20confirmed%20that%20economic%20ties%20have%20been%20affected%20by%20a%20trust%20deficit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20India%20Brings%20To%20The%20Table%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20synergy%20of%20economic%20cooperation%20has%20grown%20stronger.%20China%20remains%20a%20global%20manufacturing%20hub%20with%20prowess%20in%20technology%20and%20finance%2C%20despite%20economic%20slowdown%20and%20derisking%20by%20developed%20countries.%20Meanwhile%2C%20India's%20buoyant%20economy%20has%20grown%20more%20attractive%20for%20foreign%20investment%2C%20technology%20and%20resilient%20supply%20chains.%20China%20needs%20India's%20markets%2C%20just%20as%20India%20needs%20to%20diversify%20economic%20engagement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20has%20helped%20infrastructure%20projects%20in%20developing%20countries%2C%20but%20many%20recipients%20remain%20wary%20of%20unviable%20projects%20and%20unsustainable%20debt%20burden.%20By%20contrast%2C%20India's%20modest%20development%20assistance%2C%20focused%20on%20capacity%20building%2C%20has%20earned%20goodwill%20and%20consolidated%20its%20standing%20as%20a%20net%20security%20provider%20and%20voice%20of%20the%20Global%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20assertive%20diplomacy%20and%20territorial%20claims%20have%20raised%20concerns%20among%20its%20neighbours.%20Some%20of%20those%20neighbours%20have%20looked%20to%20India%20and%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20as%20a%20balancing%20force%20as%20they%20seek%20diplomatic%20space%20for%20a%20free%2C%20transparent%20and%20rule-based%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20The%20Two%20Co-Exist%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20and%20China%20have%20differing%20priorities%20on%20global%20governance.%20At%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20where%20China%20is%20a%20permanent%20member%20of%20the%20Security%20Council%20and%20India%20seeks%20an%20appropriate%20role%2C%20there%20is%20competition%20for%20strategic%20space.%20China%20seeks%20a%20larger%20role%20on%20the%20economic%20agenda%20but%20prefers%20the%20status%20quo%20on%20political%20and%20strategic%20issues.%20This%20contrasts%20with%20India's%20efforts%20to%20reform%20the%20multilateral%20system%20and%20bring%20the%20Global%20South%20to%20the%20high%20table%20of%20global%20governance.%20In%20strategic%20engagement%2C%20the%20divergence%20can%20expand%20as%20the%20two%20grow%20in%20stature.%20India's%20objective%20to%20build%20partnerships%20in%20a%20multipolar%20world%20contrasts%20with%20China's%20quest%20for%20global%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20its%20spectacular%20rise%20to%20major%20power%20status%2C%20China%20has%20used%20assertive%20diplomacy%20to%20fill%20a%20power%20vacuum%20and%20test%20its%20hard%20power%20capabilities.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20India's%20rise%2C%20founded%20on%20democratic%20traditions%20and%20economic%20growth%2C%20provides%20an%20alternative%20model%20of%20inclusive%20global%20governance.%20In%20the%20twenty-first%20century%2C%20the%20Indian%20narrative%20of%20%E2%80%9Ctwo%20tigers%20find%20space%20in%20the%20forest%E2%80%9D%20provides%20a%20cooperative%20and%20harmonious%20model%20for%20both%20Asia%20and%20the%20global%20community%2C%20and%20specifically%20for%20India%20and%20China%20as%20they%20seek%20to%20strike%20a%20balance%20between%20cooperation%20and%20competition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Sanjay%20Bhattacharyya%20is%20a%20former%20Indian%20diplomat.%20He%20is%20currently%20an%20independent%20consultant%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20diplomatic%20practice%20at%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20and%20a%20contributing%20author%20to%20Canadian%20think-tank%2C%20the%20Centre%20for%20International%20Governance%20Innovation.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743587640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-09%2Fmodi-xi-pti-650_650x400_61504584765.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-china-the-dragon-and-the-elephant-must-co-exist-8068903%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Today%2C%20China%20is%20the%20second%20largest%20economy%2C%20while%20India%20will%20soon%20be%20the%20third%20largest%2C%20besides%20being%20the%20two%20most%20populous%20countries.%20The%20future%20provides%20an%20opportunity%20to%20shape%20an%20emerging%20Asian%20century.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-china-the-dragon-and-the-elephant-must-co-exist-8068903%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sunny%20Deol%20says%20he%20was%20scared%20to%20make%20Gadar%202%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743587376000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119902767%2Cimgsize-36146.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2F