m%20where%20she%20sources%20her%20milk%20to%20carefully%20choose%20the%20best%20ingredients.%20%E2%80%9CA2%20milk%20was%20the%20best%20choice%20because%20it%20has%20a%20higher%20protein%20content%20and%20is%20better%20for%20the%20gut%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20science%20behind%20A2%20milk%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Samrakshini%20G%2C%20a%20gynaecologist%20and%20fertility%20specialist%20based%20in%20Bengaluru%20with%2010%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20sheds%20light%20on%20the%20ongoing%20debate%20surrounding%20the%20type%20of%20milk%20we%20consume.%20She%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CMilk%20is%20classified%20into%20two%20types%2C%20A1%20and%20A2%2C%20distinguished%20by%20a%20single%20protein%20known%20as%20beta-casein.%20The%20difference%20between%20the%20two%20lies%20in%20a%20variation%20of%20just%20one%20amino%20acid.%E2%80%9D%20In%20A1%20milk%2C%20the%20amino%20acid%20at%20position%2067%20is%20histidine%2C%20while%20in%20A2%20milk%2C%20it%20is%20proline.%20This%20seemingly%20small%20difference%20plays%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20the%20digestion%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC9393-1_11zon-1743132614-500x750.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jogurt%20contains%20monk%20fruit%20instead%20of%20sugar%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC9393-1_11zon-1743132614-500x750.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC9393-1_11zon-1743132614-200x300.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC9393-1_11zon-1743132614-768x1152.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC9393-1_11zon-1743132614-1024x1536.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC9393-1_11zon-1743132614-1366x2048.jpg%201366w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC9393-1_11zon-1743132614-1200x1800.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC9393-1_11zon-1743132614-150x225.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-416454%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EJogurt%20contains%20monk%20fruit%20instead%20of%20sugar%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20elaborates%2C%20%E2%80%9CA1%20milk%20produces%20a%20peptide%20called%20beta-casomorphin%207%20(BCM-7)%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20bloating%20and%20stomach%20discomfort.%20In%20contrast%2C%20A2%20milk%20does%20not%20produce%20this%20peptide%2C%20meaning%20it%20typically%20causes%20fewer%20digestive%20issues.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20clarify%20that%20A2%20milk%20is%20not%20lactose-free%2C%20so%20it%20is%20not%20suitable%20for%20individuals%20who%20have%20severe%20lactose%20intolerance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20health%20implications%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CSome%20studies%20suggest%20that%20A1%20milk%20could%20be%20linked%20to%20an%20increased%20risk%20of%20heart%20disease%20and%20autoimmune%20conditions%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F322755%2Fkarnataka-divaa-uthkarsha-project-surya-type-one-diabetes-awareness-for-underprivileged-kids%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EType%201%20diabetes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20findings%2C%20however%2C%20are%20based%20on%20observational%20studies%2C%20and%20more%20research%20is%20needed%20to%20draw%20definitive%20conclusions.%20That%20being%20said%2C%20current%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20A2%20milk%20is%20less%20likely%20to%20cause%20gastrointestinal%20issues.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20expert%2C%20Dr%20Pronobesh%2C%20an%20obstetrician%20and%20gynaecologist%20based%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CA2%20milk%20is%20a%20superior%20choice%20for%20gut%20health%20because%20the%20A2%20beta-casein%20is%20gentler%20on%20the%20digestive%20system.%20It%20reduces%20discomfort%20like%20bloating%2C%20gas%2C%20and%20inflammation%20in%20people%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20tolerate%20normal%20milk.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20farm%20(Deep%20Roots%20Farms%20in%20Indore)%20where%20I%20get%20my%20A2%20milk%20feeds%20organic%20produce%20to%20their%20Gir%20cows%2C%20ensuring%20it%E2%80%99s%20safe.%20The%20cows%20are%20not%20hormonally%20altered%20to%20produce%20more%20milk%20and%20are%20treated%20with%20the%20utmost%20care%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20fresh%20A2%20milk%20to%20perfect%20yoghurt%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20of%20making%20Jogurt%20is%20both%20intricate%20and%20time-consuming.%20The%20process%20begins%20by%20sourcing%20fresh%20A2%20milk%2C%20which%20is%20pasteurised.%20It%20is%20a%20process%20of%20heating%20milk%20to%20a%20specific%20temperature%20to%20kill%20harmful%20bacteria%20and%20pathogens.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20pasteurisation%2C%20I%20heat%20the%20milk%20to%2085%C2%B0C%20and%20then%20cool%20it%20down%20to%2045%C2%B0C.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20we%20add%20the%20yoghurt%20culture%20with%20specific%20probiotic%20strains%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%20The%20milk%20is%20then%20incubated%20for%2016%20hours%20in%20winter%20and%2010%20hours%20in%20summer%20to%20develop%20the%20perfect%20consistency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC01390-1_11zon-1743132730-500x750.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jogurt%20currently%20includes%2011%20flavours%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC01390-1_11zon-1743132730-500x750.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC01390-1_11zon-1743132730-200x300.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC01390-1_11zon-1743132730-768x1152.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC01390-1_11zon-1743132730-1024x1536.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC01390-1_11zon-1743132730-1365x2048.jpg%201365w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC01390-1_11zon-1743132730-1200x1800.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC01390-1_11zon-1743132730-150x225.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FDSC01390-1_11zon-1743132730.jpg%201660w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-416456%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EJogurt%20currently%20offers%2011%20flavours%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20step%20involves%20straining%20the%20yoghurt%20to%20separate%20the%20thickened%20portion%2C%20then%20whisking%20it%20to%20achieve%20a%20smooth%20consistency.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20double-strain%20it%20to%20achieve%20the%20Greek%20yoghurt%20consistency%2C%20leaving%2015%20grams%20of%20protein%20per%20100-gram%20cup%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%20proudly.%20The%20yoghurt%20is%20then%20chilled%20for%20approximately%20five%20hours%20before%20flavours%20are%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20currently%20offer%20a%20total%20of%2011%20flavours.%20To%20sweeten%20the%20yoghurt%2C%20I%20use%20monk%20fruit%20as%20a%20natural%20alternative%20and%20avoid%20using%20stevia%2C%20refined%20sugar%2C%20or%20raw%20sugar.%20For%20fruit-flavoured%20varieties%2C%20I%20